items.name: Yatsuhashi (八橋Mix)
items.description:
A more refined MBW-COS Aurora_N dpep5mzpikaz+tmnd

This mix is intended to make cute and interesting dynamic images. It has a very cute and thick textural quality, like oil pastel, and uses a sort of art style reminiscent of ZUN or other similar artists, with simple faces and layered palette swatches for shading instead of detailed linework or gradients. The example images are similar to those in MBW-COS Aurora_N dpep5mzpikaz+tmnd. However, unlike that model you do not have to invoke any loras to get this textural quality effect. As such I consider Yatsuhashi a more complete version.

Because I believe in the open-source principles of Stable Diffusion, I always list the full merge recipe for any merge I make. I recommend other people to do so also. As Yatsuhashi is part of WagaShikashi collection, you can find the full merge recipe and ingredients details here:

https://huggingface.co/Jemnite/WagaShikashi

Outfit - beret, military uniform, blue coat, armored boots

Review and comment with your experiences, I would appreciate whatever feedback you can provide in order to continue improving my technique.
Inpaint guide: if face on full body shots comes out deformed\not detailed enough - it's easily fixed with single inpaint, whole process takes half a minute. Press generate and you done!

Trained on Anything V4.5 and CLIP Skip 2.

items.name: Valeria D (WowVal)
items.description:
A commission of @findingavarice521.

Valeria D (aka WowVal) is an Instagram model and social media influencer.

1020-step TI trained on a dataset of 18 images.

Appreciate my work? My TIs are free, but you can always buy me a coffee. :)

Curious about my work process? I have summarized it here.

So... A lot has happened during these 3 weeks I've been on holidays. As some of you will have noticed, most of my TIs have been removed from the site. I'm slowly working on recovering them, but I guess it's gonna take time. Gotta say the mods have been very quick in republishing them until now, for which I really want to thank them, and I hope that won't change in the future. About 20 or so have been recovered, and I've sent requests already for more. I had more than 150 overall, so still a lot of work ahead. xD

With regards to new TIs, I'll keep uploading them for now and let's hope they won't be removed too. I'm trying to be as picky as possible with clothing and such, but let's see how it goes.

How to create a good prompt using my TIs

You're obviously free to experiment, but bear in mind that my TIs are trained with a more or less fixed phrasing, that normally starts with:

"photo of EMBEDDING_NAME, a woman"

So I recommend always starting your prompt like that and then building the rest of the prompt from there. For instance, "photo of beautiful (wowval:0.99), a woman as a movie star, hair upsweep updo, sweater off-shoulders, trousers, at a movie premiere gala, dark moody ambience (masterpiece:1.2) (photorealistic:1.2) (bokeh) (best quality) (detailed skin:1.2) (intricate details) (nighttime) (8k) (HDR) (cinematic lighting) (sharp focus), (looking at the camera:1.1), (closeup portrait:1.1)"

  • Denoise strength upscaling: 0.3 to 0.55

sarashi - Sometimes the realistic-ish models like RevAnimated don't really add the sarashi well, so you might need to tag it.

  • better representation of multiple people

  • trained size 768x768, 1024x1024

When creating the model this time more attention was paid to the aesthetics as well as multiple people, and that it looks even more real

Version 1

  • First, I created an extensive base by reading in over 5000 photos of people of various nationalities, both clothed and nude.

  • Then the first model, AmiReal, was used to generate images.

  • After determining that the shadow cast was not correct when generating the people, I used over 500 images to refine the shadow cast on bodies and objects.

  • Then I used the next model, CyberRealistic, and combined the two models.

  • Unfortunately, this combination resulted in either strange faces or the same faces over and over again.

  • So I trained the model again and took over 3000 close-up shots of faces until the result was acceptable.

  • For my last combination, I decided to use the realisticVision and realhotMix models.

  • Then I tried again to refine with 500 images only hands and feet.
